# Package System — Status After Refactoring (2026-03-25)

## Completed Steps

### Step 1: Multi-binary e2e ✓ (commit 551ea0d6)
- Built node-agent package with `extra_binaries: [globular-upgrader]`
- Published 0.0.5 to repository (47.9 MB, both binaries)
- Artifact download works through Envoy gateway (cluster_id metadata + allowlist)
- `service.install_payload` extracts both binaries to `/usr/lib/globular/bin/`
- Self-upgrade path verified: `isSelfUpgradePlan` → `delegateToUpgrader` → `/usr/lib/globular/bin/globular-upgrader`

### Step 2: Spec schema ✓ (commit 551ea0d6)
- `PackageSpec` struct in `pkgpack/packagespec.go` — canonical spec definition
- `ParseSpec()` / `ValidateSpec()` with kind-specific rules, duplicate step detection
- Wired into `ScanSpec()` (warnings) and CLI (`globular pkg validate --spec`)
- All 54 specs (32 service + 22 infra) pass validation

### Step 3: build.sh cleanup ✓ (commit 551ea0d6)
- `metadata.entrypoint` and `metadata.install_bins` fields in `SpecMetadata`
- `ScanSpec` honors entrypoint override chain: metadata → top-level → discovery
- `entrypoint: noop` + `install_bins: false` for scylladb, keepalived
- `build.sh` reduced from 46-line if/elif chain to zero special cases
- All 22 infra specs now have explicit `metadata.name`

### Step 4: Installer spec sync ✓ (installer commit 17d4f36)
- `make sync-specs` copies from both `packages/specs/` and `services/generated/specs/`
- 20 missing service specs added, 25 stale specs refreshed (45 total)
- `make check-specs` CI gate — lists every stale/missing spec, fails with actionable message
- Installer builds clean with all specs

### Step 5: Unified build (covered)
- `build.sh` is now a trivial metadata-driven loop
- `build-all-packages.sh` orchestrates both infra + service builds
- `make sync-specs` keeps installer in sync

---

## Auth fixes that fell out of e2e testing

### Artifact download auth (commit 551ea0d6)
- `auth_context.go`: read `cluster_id` from gRPC metadata as fallback (Envoy strips mTLS)
- `artifact.go`: inject `cluster_id` metadata + mTLS client certs into download requests
- `repository/server.go`: `DownloadArtifact` added to unauthenticated allowlist (read-only, cluster_id-protected)

### Invariant probe fixes (commits 04478750, 0cf3d183, e8dc1162)
- Log invariant failure reason on each retry attempt (was silent before)
- TCP probe skips gracefully on missing/incomplete service configs (was hard failure)
- Probe retry with 3s settle delay after service restart (3x3s = 9s window)

---

## Remaining items (not blocking)

### Archive naming convention
`service.etcd_3.5.14_linux_amd64.tgz` — the `service.` prefix is wrong for infrastructure and commands.
Should be `<name>_<version>_<platform>.tgz`. Low priority, backward-compatible change.
Needs: update `buildArchiveName()` in `builder.go` + installer expectations.

### Installer package embedding
`internal/assets/packages/` has 57 pre-built .tgz files, manually synced.
Future: add `make embed-packages` target that builds from source and verifies checksums.
This is a CI/build automation task, not a code change.

### Port config drift
Some service configs have stale port assignments (e.g. ai-watcher config said 10210,
service bound to 10211). The TCP probe now handles this gracefully but the root cause
is `ensureServicePortConfig` creating stubs that diverge from runtime.
Future: reconcile service configs against actual listening ports on startup.
